            <title>[SOLR-278] LukeRequest/Response for handling show=schema</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-278</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;the soon to be attached patch adds a method to LukeRequest to set the option for showing schema from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-266&quot; title=&quot;Let the LukeRequestHandler return parsed schema information&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-266&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-266&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  the patch also modifies LukeRepsonse to handle the schema info in the same manner as the fields from the &apos;normal&apos; luke response.  i think it&apos;s worth talking about unifying the response format so that they aren&apos;t different but that&apos;s a larger discussion.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
